This paper deals with the security of blockchain incentive mechanisms, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of deep reinforcement learning suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the analysis of complex systems, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning implies a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
